    cito:cites <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5821217>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5821223>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5821219> ;
    dc:creator "Zettel, Herbert; Laciny, Alice" ;
    dc:title "Eyarinella Zettel & Laciny 2021, gen. nov." ;
    trt:definesTaxonConcept <http://taxon-concept.plazi.org/id/Animalia/Eyarinella_Zettel_2021> ;
    trt:publishedIn <http://dx.doi.org/10.37520/aemnp.2021.029> ;
    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.37520/aemnp.2021.029>
    bibo:endPage "527" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2021-12-31" ;
    bibo:startPage "517" ;
    bibo:volume "61" ;
    dc:creator "Zettel, Herbert; Laciny, Alice" ;
    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "The taxonomy of some unusual Microveliinae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Veliidae) from India" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5821217>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5821223>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5821219> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5821217>
    dc:description "Figs 1–4. Habitus of Thirumalaia ocularis gen. nov. & sp. nov. (1 – apterous male, 2 – apterous female), and of Eyarinella robusta gen. nov. & sp. nov. (3 – apterous male, 4 – apterous female)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5821217/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5821223>
    dc:description "Figs 16–24. Structural details of Eyarinella robusta gen. nov. & sp. nov.: 16 – head, first antennomere, and pronotum, dorsal; 17 – head and anterior margin of pronotum, lateral; 18 – foreleg of male (arrow points at proximal end of grasping comb); 19 – metafemur of male; 20 – abdominal segments 6–8, and proctiger of female, dorsal; 21 – abdominal segment 8 of male, ventral; 22 – pygophore of male, ventral; 23 – proctiger of male, dorsal; 24 – left paramere, lateral. Pilosity omitted, except in Fig. 24." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5821223/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5821219>
    dc:description "Figs 5–8. Habitus of Geovelia fikaceki sp. nov. (5 – apterous male, 6 – apterous female), and Neoalardus typicus (Distant, 1903) (7 – apterous male, 8 – apterous female), both specimens from India." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5821219/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

